{"questionId":"9066390","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Dinitrogen monoxide, N<sub>2</sub>O, causes depletion of ozone in the stratosphere.</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">The Lewis (electron dot) structure of the dinitrogen monoxide molecule can be represented as:</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><img style=\"margin-right:auto;margin-left:auto;display:block;\" src=\"https://ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/5985/3d.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"373\" height=\"54\"></span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">State, giving a reason, the shape of the dinitrogen monoxide molecule.</span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">linear <em><strong>AND</strong> </em>2 electron domains</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><em><strong>OR</strong></em></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">linear <em><strong>AND</strong> </em>2 regions of electron density &nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong>Accept “two bonds </span><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><strong>AND</strong></span> <span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">no lone pairs” for reason.</span></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9066390","referenceCode":"19M.2.hl.TZ2.d(ii)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"State, giving a reason, the shape of the dinitrogen monoxide molecule.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"d(ii)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 4: Chemical bonding and structure","4.3 Covalent structures","Core","Topic 4: Chemical bonding and structure"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}